                  </hi>. I am a policeman. I was called, and saw the pri<lb></lb>soner and prosecutor in the passage—the prisoner was fumbling under his apron, as if trying to get some money into his pocket—I took hold of his hand, and heard some money jink into his left trowsers' pocket—he was endeavouring to conceal it—it was 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoners Defence.</hi> I had no hand in my pocket; I went for some tobacco, rapped at the door, and went in, as no one answered.</p>
